article.headline: Davidson 66, Elon 45
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- De'Mon Brooks scored 25 points, grabbed a game-high 10 boards and recorded four steals as Davidson beat Elon 66-45 on Thursday night. Clint Mann chipped in with 12 points and six rebounds as Davidson grabbed 20 offensive boards in the win. Davidson (21-7, 15-2 Southern Conference) led by just three, 31-28, at halftime, but opened the second half on a 22-9 run. Brooks capped the run with two free throws as the Wildcats took a 53-37 lead with 11:33 left to play. Brooks scored 15 points during the run and Mann added six. Davidson outrebounded Elon 50-35 and forced the Phoenix to turn the ball over 15 times. Lucas Troutman paced Elon (13-15, 8-9) with 15 points but no other Phoenix scored more than six points. Davidson leads the all-time series 34-13 and have won the last two matchups against the Phoenix.
